**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **Environment Isolation**:
```java
@Configuration
@Profile("!production")
class DevelopmentSecurityConfig {
    // Relaxed security for development only
    @Bean
    public SecurityFilterChain devFilterChain(HttpSecurity http) throws Exception {
        http.authorizeHttpRequests(authz -> authz.anyRequest().permitAll());
        return http.build();
    }
}

@Configuration  
@Profile("production")
class ProductionStartupValidator implements ApplicationListener<ApplicationReadyEvent> {
    @Override
    public void onApplicationEvent(ApplicationReadyEvent event) {
        // Verify production requirements at startup
        Environment env = event.getApplicationContext().getEnvironment();
        if (!env.getProperty("server.ssl.enabled", Boolean.class, false)) {
            throw new IllegalStateException("SSL must be enabled in production");
        }
    }
}
```

2. **Secrets Management Integration**:
```java
@Configuration
@Profile("production")
class VaultConfiguration {

    @Bean
    public DataSource dataSource(VaultTemplate vaultTemplate) {
        VaultResponse response = vaultTemplate.read("secret/database");
        Map<String, Object> data = response.getData();

        HikariDataSource ds = new HikariDataSource();
        ds.setJdbcUrl((String) data.get("url"));
        ds.setUsername((String) data.get("username"));
        ds.setPassword((String) data.get("password"));
        return ds;
    }
}
```

3. **Runtime Security Monitoring**:
```java
@Component
@Profile("production")
class SecurityEventListener {

    private static final Logger auditLog = LoggerFactory.getLogger("SECURITY_AUDIT");
    private final MeterRegistry meterRegistry;

    public SecurityEventListener(MeterRegistry meterRegistry) {
        this.meterRegistry = meterRegistry;
    }

    @EventListener
    public void onAuthenticationFailure(AuthenticationFailureBadCredentialsEvent event) {
        String username = event.getAuthentication().getName();
        auditLog.warn("Failed login attempt for user: {}", username);
        meterRegistry.counter("security.auth.failures", "reason", "bad_credentials").increment();
    }

    @EventListener
    public void onAuthorizationFailure(AuthorizationDeniedEvent event) {
        Authentication auth = event.getAuthentication().get();
        auditLog.warn("Access denied for user: {} to resource: {}", 
            auth.getName(), event.getSource());
        meterRegistry.counter("security.authz.denials").increment();
    }
}
```

**Additional Protections**:
- **Actuator on separate port (9090)**: Prevents accidental exposure through main application port
- **Randomized actuator path**: `/internal/ops/${ACTUATOR_SECRET_PATH}` prevents enumeration attacks
- **Startup validation**: Application fails to start if security requirements aren't met
- **Connection pool monitoring**: Detects potential connection exhaustion attacks
- **Error message sanitization**: Never expose stack traces or internal details to clients
- **HSTS preload**: Ensures browsers always use HTTPS after first visit
- **Prometheus metrics**: Security events tracked for alerting and dashboards
